==Russian==

===Pronunciation===
* {{ru-IPA-manual|[ʲ]}}

===Letter===
{{head|ru|letter|lower case||upper case|Ь}}

# {{Cyrl-def|ru|letter|30|мягкий знак}}

====Usage notes====
* The soft sign has no sound of its own, but modifies that of the preceding consonant by causing it to be pronounced [[palatalized]] (i.e. soft).
* Less commonly, it just has a traditional orthographic usage with no phonetic meaning. For example, nouns ending in {{orth|ч}}, {{orth|ш}}, {{orth|ж}} and {{orth|щ}} are pronounced identically to their counterparts ending in {{orth|чь}}, {{orth|шь}}, {{orth|жь}} and {{orth|щь}}, but they have different grammatical genders and declensions.
* It also has the function of a [[separation sign]]: vowels after the soft sign are pronounced separately from the previous consonant and are [[iotated]]. Compare {{m|ru|лить|льют}} {{IPAchar|[lʲjut]}} and {{m|ru|лютый|лют}} {{IPAchar|[lʲut]}}.

===See also===
* {{l|ru|ъ|tr=-}} {{q|hard sign}}
